01:37:32,424 --> 01:37:34,664
WILLIAM:Don't even think about it.
Go away immediately.

1438
01:37:34,744 --> 01:37:37,264
- Go away.
MR. SMITH:- Right.

1439
01:37:37,344 --> 01:37:39,224
MR. SMITH:Sorry.

1440
01:37:41,384 --> 01:37:43,704
WILLIAM:You were saying?

1441
01:37:46,104 --> 01:37:49,424
ANNA:Yes.

1442
01:37:49,504 --> 01:37:52,224
ANNA:I have to go away today, but l...

1443
01:37:52,304 --> 01:37:55,464
ANNA:wondered if I didn't...

1444
01:37:55,544 --> 01:37:59,744
ANNA:whether you might
let me see you a little,

1445
01:37:59,824 --> 01:38:02,585
ANNA:or... a lot, maybe.

1446
01:38:05,705 --> 01:38:08,505
ANNA:See if you could like me again.

1447
01:38:08,545 --> 01:38:10,905
WILLIAM:But yesterday
that actor asked you who I was,

1448
01:38:10,945 --> 01:38:13,585
WILLIAM:and you just
dismissed me out of hand.

1449
01:38:14,905 --> 01:38:17,905
WILLIAM:I heard.

1450
01:38:17,945 --> 01:38:21,025
WILLIAM:You had a microphone.
I had headphones.

1451
01:38:21,105 --> 01:38:23,025
ANNA:You expect me
to tell the truth about my life...

1452
01:38:23,065 --> 01:38:25,585
ANNA:to the most indiscreet man
in England?

1453
01:38:26,945 --> 01:38:29,186
MARTIN:Uh, excuse me.

1454
01:38:29,266 --> 01:38:31,586
MARTIN:It's your mother on the phone.

1455
01:38:34,266 --> 01:38:36,306
WILLIAM:Will you tell her
I'll ring her back?

1456
01:38:36,346 --> 01:38:39,346
MARTIN:I've actually tried that tack, but
she said you've said that once before,

1457
01:38:39,386 --> 01:38:41,306
MARTIN:and it's now been about 24 hours...

1458
01:38:41,346 --> 01:38:44,666
MARTIN:and the foot that was purple
is now sort of blackish in color and--

1459
01:38:44,706 --> 01:38:48,306
WILLIAM:Right, right. Yeah.
Perfect timing, as ever.

1460
01:38:50,426 --> 01:38:53,106
WILLIAM:Martin, hold the fort a second.

1461
01:38:53,146 --> 01:38:55,426
WILLIAM:Uh, yes. All right.

1462
01:39:00,347 --> 01:39:02,787
MARTIN:Um, could I just say--

1463
01:39:02,867 --> 01:39:07,707
MARTIN:[ Chuckles ] I thought Ghost
was the most wonderful film.

1464
01:39:08,907 --> 01:39:11,467
ANNA:- Is that right?
MARTIN:- Oh, yes.

1466
01:39:14,547 --> 01:39:18,267
MARTIN:Um, I've always wondered...

1467
01:39:18,347 --> 01:39:21,427
MARTIN:what Patrick Swayze's like
in-- in-- in real life.

1468
01:39:21,467 --> 01:39:24,987
ANNA:I can't say that I know Patrick
all that well.

1469
01:39:25,067 --> 01:39:27,228
MARTIN:He wasn't that friendly during filming?

1470
01:39:27,308 --> 01:39:32,508
ANNA:Well, I'm sure he was friendly to
Demi Moore who acted with him in Ghost.

1471
01:39:34,908 --> 01:39:37,148
MARTIN:Oh. Oh, right.

1472
01:39:37,228 --> 01:39:39,068
MARTIN:Sorry.

1473
01:39:40,668 --> 01:39:43,788
MARTIN:Always been a bit of an ass.
[ Chuckling ]

1474
01:39:43,868 --> 01:39:46,708
MARTIN:Um, anyway-- Um--

1475
01:39:46,748 --> 01:39:48,628
MARTIN:Well, it was lovely to meet you.

1476
01:39:48,668 --> 01:39:51,028
MARTIN:I'm a huge, huge fan of yours.

1477
01:39:51,068 --> 01:39:54,549
MARTIN:And Demi's, of course.

1478
01:39:56,989 --> 01:39:59,109
WILLIAM:Sorry.

1479
01:39:59,189 --> 01:40:00,949
ANNA:WILLIAM:That's fine.

1480
01:40:01,029 --> 01:40:04,669
ANNA:There's always a pause when the jury
goes out to consider their verdict.

1481
01:40:06,869 --> 01:40:09,909
WILLIAM:Anna, look, um--

1482
01:40:09,949 --> 01:40:13,589
WILLIAM:I'm a fairly levelheaded bloke,

1483
01:40:13,669 --> 01:40:17,389
WILLIAM:not often in and out of love.

1484
01:40:17,469 --> 01:40:19,509
WILLIAM:But, uh--

1485
01:40:23,870 --> 01:40:26,150
WILLIAM:Can I just say no to your...

1486
01:40:26,230 --> 01:40:30,390
WILLIAM:kind request and, uh, leave it at that?

1487
01:40:33,630 --> 01:40:36,830
ANNA:Yes.

1488
01:40:36,910 --> 01:40:40,310
ANNA:Fine. Of course. I--

1489
01:40:40,350 --> 01:40:42,350
ANNA:Of course.

1490
01:40:43,990 --> 01:40:46,910
ANNA:I'll just be going, then.
It was nice to see you.

1491
01:40:46,990 --> 01:40:49,790
WILLIAM:The thing is,

1492
01:40:49,870 --> 01:40:53,191
WILLIAM:with you I'm in real... danger.

1493
01:40:53,271 --> 01:40:56,311
WILLIAM:It seems like a... perfect situation,

1494
01:40:56,391 --> 01:40:59,711
WILLIAM:apart from that
foul temper of yours, but...

1495
01:40:59,791 --> 01:41:04,151
WILLIAM:my relatively inexperienced heart
would, I fear, not...

1496
01:41:04,231 --> 01:41:06,911
WILLIAM:recover, uh, if I was...

1497
01:41:06,991 --> 01:41:10,871
WILLIAM:once again cast aside,
as I would absolutely expect to be.

1498
01:41:10,951 --> 01:41:15,911
WILLIAM:There are just too many pictures of you,
too many films.

1499
01:41:15,991 --> 01:41:19,191
WILLIAM:You'd go and I'd be, uh,

1500
01:41:19,271 --> 01:41:21,792
WILLIAM:well, buggered, basically.

1501
01:41:23,232 --> 01:41:26,072
ANNA:That really is a real no, isn't it?

1502
01:41:26,112 --> 01:41:30,632
WILLIAM:I live in Notting Hill.
You live in... Beverly Hills.

1503
01:41:30,712 --> 01:41:32,552
WILLIAM:Everyone in the world
knows who you are.

1504
01:41:32,632 --> 01:41:36,192
WILLIAM:My mother has trouble
remembering my name.

1505
01:41:36,272 --> 01:41:38,112
ANNA:Fine.

1506
01:41:39,912 --> 01:41:44,072
ANNA:Fine. Good decision.
Good decision.

1507
01:41:47,632 --> 01:41:51,033
ANNA:The fame thing isn't really real,
you know?

1508
01:41:54,673 --> 01:41:58,153
ANNA:And don't forget I'm--

1509
01:41:58,233 --> 01:42:01,873
ANNA:I'm also just a girl...

1510
01:42:01,953 --> 01:42:05,913
ANNA:standing in front of a boy...

1511
01:42:05,993 --> 01:42:08,473
ANNA:asking him to love her.

1512
01:42:18,914 --> 01:42:20,754
Good-bye.

1513
01:42:42,194 --> 01:42:44,554
WILLIAM:So what do you think?
Good move?

1514
01:42:44,594 --> 01:42:46,795
HONEY:[ Honey ]
Yeah, good move.

1515
01:42:46,875 --> 01:42:49,475
HONEY:I mean, when all's said and done,
she's nothing special.

1516
01:42:49,515 --> 01:42:51,395
HONEY:I saw her taking her trousers down,

1517
01:42:51,435 --> 01:42:54,195
HONEY:and I definitely glimpsed
some cellulite down there.

1518
01:42:54,275 --> 01:42:56,995
BELLA:Good decision, yeah.

1519
01:42:57,035 --> 01:42:59,395
BELLA:All actresses are as mad as snakes.

1520
01:42:59,435 --> 01:43:02,395
WILLIAM:- Tones, what do you reckon?
TONY:- Never met her, never want to.

1521
01:43:02,475 --> 01:43:06,035
WILLIAM:- Brilliant. Max?
MAX:- Absolutely. Never trust a vegetarian.

1522
01:43:06,115 --> 01:43:08,715
WILLIAM:Great. Thanks. Brilliant.

1523
01:43:09,995 --> 01:43:12,395
