1557
01:45:20,600 --> 01:45:22,840
BELLA:- [ Bella ] Which way are you going?

1558
01:45:22,920 --> 01:45:25,960
MAX:Down Kensington Church Street, then
Knightsbridge, then Hyde Park Corner.

1559
01:45:26,000 --> 01:45:28,560
BELLA:- No, crazy. Go along Bayswater.
HONEY:- That's right. Then Park Lane.

1560
01:45:28,640 --> 01:45:30,600
BERNIE:No, straight down to the Cromwell Road,
then left.

1561
01:45:30,680 --> 01:45:32,600
WILLIAM:- No!

1562
01:45:33,960 --> 01:45:37,481
MAX:Stop right there!
I will decide the route. All right?

1563
01:45:37,521 --> 01:45:39,681
Sorry, Max.

1564
01:45:39,761 --> 01:45:42,561
MAX:James Bond never has to put up
with this sort of shit.

1567
01:45:49,361 --> 01:45:51,801
- [ Bella ] Turn right!

1568
01:45:51,881 --> 01:45:53,321
- I can't. It's one way.
- Do a U-turn.

1569
01:45:53,361 --> 01:45:56,041
- Oh, sod it. Hold on.

1572
01:46:01,681 --> 01:46:04,721
- Brilliant!

1575
01:46:09,202 --> 01:46:12,482
BERNIE:- Bloody hell, this is fun!

1576
01:46:12,562 --> 01:46:14,402
- Sorry.

1577
01:46:14,482 --> 01:46:16,682
WILLIAM:Hi.
Is Miss Scott staying here?

1578
01:46:16,722 --> 01:46:20,002
RITZ MAN:- No, sir.
WILLIAM:- How 'bout Miss Flintstone?

1579
01:46:20,082 --> 01:46:22,962
RITZ MAN:- No, sir.
WILLIAM:- Uh, Bambi?

1580
01:46:23,042 --> 01:46:26,042
WILLIAM:- No, sir.
WILLIAM:- Or, um--

1581
01:46:26,122 --> 01:46:30,082
WILLIAM:I don't know.
Beavis or Butt-head?

1582
01:46:30,162 --> 01:46:32,882
RITZ MAN:No, sir.

1583
01:46:32,922 --> 01:46:35,483
WILLIAM:Thanks. Thanks.

1584
01:46:35,563 --> 01:46:38,083
RITZ MAN:There was a Miss Pocahontas,

1585
01:46:38,163 --> 01:46:40,683
RITZ MAN:but she checked out
about an hour ago.

1586
01:46:40,723 --> 01:46:43,363
RITZ MAN:I believe she's holding
a press conference at the Savoy...

1587
01:46:43,443 --> 01:46:46,363
RITZ MAN:before flying to America.

1588
01:46:50,483 --> 01:46:52,363
BERNIE:We have liftoff.

1590
01:47:01,083 --> 01:47:03,004
You have message for Takiama?

1591
01:47:03,084 --> 01:47:05,164
I'll just check, sir.

1595
01:47:27,324 --> 01:47:29,604
SPIKE:Bugger this for a bunch of bananas.

1596
01:47:33,725 --> 01:47:37,325
Stop! Stop! Stop!
Stay there! Go! Go!

1597
01:47:37,365 --> 01:47:40,525
HONEY:- Whoa, whoa, whoa! Hang on!

1598
01:47:40,565 --> 01:47:43,485
HONEY:Come on! No! Wait! Wait there!

1599
01:47:43,565 --> 01:47:45,605
MAX:Come on! Come on! Wait!

1600
01:47:45,685 --> 01:47:48,685
Whoa, whoa, whoa! Go on!
Through, through!

1601
01:47:50,285 --> 01:47:52,725
You're my hero!

1602
01:47:52,805 --> 01:47:54,645
Whoa! Down boy.

1610
01:48:13,566 --> 01:48:15,446
WILLIAM:- Excuse me.

1611
01:48:15,486 --> 01:48:18,046
- Yes?
WILLIAM:- Where's the press conference, please?

1612
01:48:18,126 --> 01:48:21,126
MAN AT SAVOY:- Are you an accredited
member of the press?
- Yep.

1613
01:48:22,606 --> 01:48:26,886
MAN AT SAVOY:- There you go.
- That's a Blockbuster Video
membership card, sir.

1614
01:48:26,966 --> 01:48:29,967
WILLIAM:That's right.
I work for their in-house magazine.

1615
01:48:30,007 --> 01:48:32,207
WILLIAM:- Movies Are Our Business.
MAN AT SAVOY:- I'm sorry, sir.

1616
01:48:32,247 --> 01:48:34,647
BELLA:- He's with me.
MAN AT SAVOY:- And you are?

1617
01:48:34,727 --> 01:48:38,887
BELLA:Writing an article on how London hotels
treat people in wheelchairs.

1618
01:48:39,847 --> 01:48:42,887
MAN AT SAVOY:Yes, of course, madam.
It's in the Lancaster Room.

1619
01:48:42,967 --> 01:48:45,287
MAN AT SAVOY:Though I'm afraid you're rather late.

1620
01:48:45,367 --> 01:48:47,207
Run!

1622
01:49:01,888 --> 01:49:05,568
HONEY:[ Man ] Does this mean that Miss Scott
will not be publicizing her next film?

1623
01:49:05,648 --> 01:49:07,768
No, it absolutely
does not mean that.

1624
01:49:07,848 --> 01:49:09,968
She'll be abiding by
all her present commitments.

1625
01:49:10,008 --> 01:49:13,768
She just won't be making
any more for the next year.

1626
01:49:13,848 --> 01:49:15,848
JEREMY:HONEY:[ Man #2 ]
When will the film be released?

1627
01:49:15,928 --> 01:49:18,128
JEREMY:[ Publicist ] At the moment,
the plan is to release in America...

1628
01:49:18,168 --> 01:49:20,048
towards the end of the autumn,

1629
01:49:20,088 --> 01:49:23,288
and over here around Christmas
or early in the new year.

1630
01:49:23,328 --> 01:49:25,328
JEREMY:Right! Dominic.

1631
01:49:25,409 --> 01:49:28,449
QUESTIONER 1:Anna, how much longer are you
staying in the U.K., then?

1632
01:49:28,529 --> 01:49:30,369
ANNA:No time at all.
I leave tonight.

1633
01:49:30,449 --> 01:49:35,169
JEREMY:Which is why we have to round things
up now, so final questions, please.

1634
01:49:35,249 --> 01:49:36,889
QUESTIONER  2:Yes. Lady there.

1635
01:49:36,929 --> 01:49:39,689
QUESTIONER  2:Is your decision to take
a year off anything to do...

1636
01:49:39,769 --> 01:49:42,889
QUESTIONER  2:with the rumors about Jeff
and his present leading lady?

1637
01:49:42,969 --> 01:49:46,249
ANNA:- Absolutely not.
QUESTIONER 2:- Do you believe the rumors?

1638
01:49:46,329 --> 01:49:50,009
ANNA:Well, it's really
not my business anymore.

1639
01:49:50,089 --> 01:49:54,690
ANNA:Though I will say, from my experience,
rumors about Jeff do tend to be true.

1641
01:49:57,290 --> 01:50:01,130
QUESTIONER 3:Yeah. The last time you were here, there
were some fairly graphic photographs...

1642
01:50:01,210 --> 01:50:05,050
QUESTIONER 3:taken of you
with a young English guy.

1643
01:50:05,130 --> 01:50:08,130
QUESTIONER 3:So, uh, what happened there?

1644
01:50:08,210 --> 01:50:11,450
ANNA:He was just a friend.
We're still friends, I think.

1645
01:50:11,530 --> 01:50:14,650
- Right, um--

1646
01:50:14,690 --> 01:50:17,010
JEREMY:Yes. Gentleman in the pink shirt.

1647
01:50:22,450 --> 01:50:26,771
WILLIAM:Yes. Miss Scott,

1648
01:50:26,851 --> 01:50:29,211
WILLIAM:are there any circumstances in which...

1649
01:50:29,251 --> 01:50:32,091
WILLIAM:the two of you...

1650
01:50:32,131 --> 01:50:35,171
WILLIAM:might be more than just good friends?

1651
01:50:36,891 --> 01:50:41,451
ANNA:I hoped there would be, but no,
I'm... assured there aren't.

1652
01:50:41,531 --> 01:50:44,931
WILLIAM:- But what would you say if--
JEREMY:- Sorry. Just the one question, please.

1653
01:50:45,011 --> 01:50:47,491
ANNA:No, it's all right.
You were saying.

1654
01:50:49,171 --> 01:50:52,092
WILLIAM:I was just wondering if, uh,

1655
01:50:52,172 --> 01:50:55,772
OTHER JOURNALIST:WILLIAM:it turned out that this person, uh--

1656
01:50:55,852 --> 01:50:57,732
OTHER JOURNALIST:[ Man #3 ]
Thacker. His name was Thacker.

1657
01:50:57,812 --> 01:50:59,852
WILLIAM:- Thanks, thanks.

1658
01:50:59,932 --> 01:51:02,492
WILLIAM:I just wondered whether if...

1659
01:51:02,532 --> 01:51:06,332
WILLIAM:Mr. Thacker realized he'd been
a daft prick...

1661
01:51:08,692 --> 01:51:11,972
WILLIAM:and got down on his knees and...
begged you to reconsider,

1662
01:51:12,052 --> 01:51:15,652
WILLIAM:whether you would, in fact, then...

1663
01:51:15,732 --> 01:51:17,692
WILLIAM:reconsider?

1664
01:51:26,813 --> 01:51:29,853
ANNA:- Yes, I believe I would.

1665
01:51:31,973 --> 01:51:34,933
WILLIAM:That's very good news.
Um--

1666
01:51:36,333 --> 01:51:39,613
WILLIAM:The readers of Horse & Hound
will be absolutely delighted.

1668
01:51:46,213 --> 01:51:49,574
JEREMY:Right. Uh, Dominic, if you'd
like to ask your question again?

1669
01:51:49,654 --> 01:51:54,814
QUESTIONER 1:Yeah? Anna, how long are you
intending to stay here in Britain?

1670
01:52:02,400 --> 01:52:04,454
ANNA:Indefinitely.

1674
01:52:24,535 --> 01:52:27,735
SPIKE:- What happened?

1675
01:52:27,775 --> 01:52:29,695
HONEY:- it was good.
